author: Nerdstalgic
description:
That ‘70s Show was one of the most beloved sitcoms of the early 2000s, launching the careers of stars like Ashton Kutcher, Mila Kunis, and Topher Grace. But while the series had a strong eight-season run, it also had its fair share of ups and downs—including two failed spin-offs that fans would rather forget.  From  perfect episodes, to worst episodes, to why Eric Forman left the show in the first place, we cover it all.  

💬 What’s your favorite That ‘70s Show episode? Let us know in the comments!

🔥 Like, subscribe, and hit the bell for more deep dives into TV’s most iconic shows!
